== Eclipse ==

1. Install gradle plugin for eclipse. See for info
    https://github.com/spring-projects/eclipse-integration-gradle/

2. Import gradle project and select this directory

3. Click on build model. You might need to edit local.properties to
   make sdk.dir point to the correct location for the Android SDK

4. Add google play services as Android project from existing source

5. Add Android Support Library and import android support v7 appcompat

   <sdk>/extras/android/support/v7/appcompat/


== Commandline ==

1. Set ANDROID_HOME variable to Android SDK location:

  export ANDROID_HOME=/opt/adt-bundle-linux-latest/sdk/

2. Run project

   On the desktop: 
   
     gradle desktop:run

   On an android device:

     gradle android:installDebug android:run

== VIM ==

1. Setup pathogen

   mkdir -p ~/.vim/autoload ~/.vim/bundle && \
   curl -LSso ~/.vim/autoload/pathogen.vim https://tpo.pe/pathogen.vim

2. Add following to .vimrc

   execute pathogen#infect()

3. Install plugins:

   cd ~/.vim/bundle
   git clone https://github.com/scrooloose/syntastic.git
   git clone https://github.com/adragomir/javacomplete.git
   git clone https://github.com/scrooloose/nerdtree.git

4. Make sure libraries are available

   ./gradlew copyToLib

5. Include classpaths

   export CLASSPATH=$CLASSPATH:desktop/lib/*:core/lib/*

6. Execute vim from project's top dir

7. (Extra) Zenburn color scheme

   cd ~/.vim
   git clone https://github.com/jnurmine/Zenburn.git
   mv Zenburn/colors .
   rm -rf Zenburn

8. (Extra) Add folowing to .vimrc to use Zenburn color scheme

   colors zenburn

9. (Extra) Setup powerline

   cd ~/.vim/bundle
   git clone https://github.com/Lokaltog/powerline.git

10. (Extra) Add following to .vimrc to use poweline

   set rtp+=/home/martijn/.vim/bundle/powerline/bindings/vim
